<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AAD7FBEDFE8CB831" bold="true" box="[189,310,1082,1108]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="122836C01F196D39AAD7FBBCFE17B91A" blockId="2.[189,1399,1130,1407]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39AAD7FBBCFE94B8E1" authority="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin, 2018" authorityName="Kanesharatnam &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2018" box="[189,302,1131,1156]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavirecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AAD7FBBCFE94B8E1" box="[189,302,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bavirecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3BD057A91F196D39AB5DFBBDFE1FB8E1" box="[311,421,1130,1156]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles other 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39A818FBBDFD72B8E1" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[626,712,1130,1156]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" rank="tribe" tribe="Baviini">Baviini</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39A8B6FBBCFC7FB8E1" authority="Simon, 1877" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" box="[732,965,1130,1156]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A8B6FBBCFC9AB8E1" box="[732,800,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bavia</emphasis>
Simon, 1877
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39A9B9FBBDFB48B8E0" authority="Thorell, 1885" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1885" box="[979,1266,1130,1157]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Piranthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A9B9FBBDFBFDB8E1" box="[979,1095,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Piranthus</emphasis>
Thorell, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39AF69FBBDFEE3B8CD" authority="Simon, 1885" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stagetilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AF69FBBDFACDB8E1" box="[1283,1399,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Stagetilus</emphasis>
Simon, 1885
</taxonomicName>
), some Viciriini Simon, 1901 and some Marpissina Simon, 1901 by the flattened body form, broad oval prosoma, tubular abdomen and enlarged front legs (
<bibRefCitation id="76064B311F196D39AE65FB66FB68B8A9" author="Maddison W. P." box="[1039,1234,1201,1228]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="231 - 292" refId="ref8308" refString="Maddison W. P. 2015. A phylogenetic classification of jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology 43: 231 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / arac- 43 - 03 - 231 - 292" type="journal article" year="2015">Maddison 2015</bibRefCitation>
). However, it can readily be distinguished from them by the following combination of characters: prosoma dorsally with a lighter trapezoid (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39ABB4FB2EFDFAB976" box="[478,576,1273,1299]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[274,1314,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., Ƌ. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. Palp, ventral view. E. Palp, retrolateral view. The arrowheads point to the dorsal trapezoid (A) and black blotches (D). Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39A827FB2EFDCEB976" box="[589,628,1273,1299]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1386,302,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1398,302,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, ventral view. Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–D = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827807/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">3A</figureCitation>
), comparably long RTA, broad proximal lobe with black blotches (glands, arrow in 
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39ABE3FACAFE5EB952" box="[393,484,1309,1335]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[274,1314,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., Ƌ. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. Palp, ventral view. E. Palp, retrolateral view. The arrowheads point to the dorsal trapezoid (A) and black blotches (D). Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), well-developed prolateral lobe of bulbus (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39A9B5FACAFB99B952" box="[991,1059,1309,1335]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[274,1314,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., Ƌ. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. Palp, ventral view. E. Palp, retrolateral view. The arrowheads point to the dorsal trapezoid (A) and black blotches (D). Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 1</figureCitation>
D–E, 2A–B), small, rounded atrium at anterior portion of epigynum, relatively long copulatory ducts and pear-shaped spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39AAAFFAB3FEB5B91A" box="[197,271,1380,1407]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[248,1366,264,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[220,1367,242,1912]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov. A. Palp, ventral view. B. Palp, retrolateral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827805/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 2</figureCitation>
C–D, 3C–D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A8D654B1F196D39AAD7FA70FD37BA52" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="122836C01F196D39AAD7FA70FEFEB9A4" blockId="2.[189,324,1447,1473]" box="[189,324,1447,1473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="496081AC1F196D39AAD7FA70FEFEB9A4" bold="true" box="[189,324,1447,1473]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AAD7FA70FEFEB9A4" bold="true" box="[189,324,1447,1473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="122836C01F196D39AAD7FA01FD37BA52" blockId="2.[189,1399,1494,1592]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
A combination of the prefix ‘ 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A876FA01FDF5B995" box="[540,591,1494,1520]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">bavi</emphasis>
’ and the suffix ‘ 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A97DFA00FCE8B995" box="[791,850,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">recta</emphasis>
’. ‘ 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A91CFA00FC16B995" box="[886,940,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bavi</emphasis>
’ is taken from 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39AE0FFA00FB13B995" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" box="[1125,1193,1495,1520]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AE0FFA00FB13B995" box="[1125,1193,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bavia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and refers to the 
<taxonomicName id="D5974D431F196D39AAD7FA2DFEBBBA76" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" box="[189,257,1530,1555]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AAD7FA2DFEBBBA76" box="[189,257,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bavia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like appearance of members of the genus. ‘ 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A897FA2DFCFABA76" box="[765,832,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Recta</emphasis>
’ is derived from the Latin, meaning straight, and refers to the orientation of the embolus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A8D654B1F196D38AAD7F988FCFFBD2C" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="122836C01F196D39AAD7F988FEF4BA1C" blockId="2.[189,334,1631,1657]" box="[189,334,1631,1657]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="496081AC1F196D39AAD7F988FEF4BA1C" bold="true" box="[189,334,1631,1657]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AAD7F988FEF4BA1C" bold="true" box="[189,334,1631,1657]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="122836C01F196D38AAD7F958FCFFBD2C" blockId="2.[189,1399,1678,2027]" lastBlockId="3.[189,1399,267,329]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Large, flattened foliage-dwellers. Prosoma oval, relatively flat, with central lighter trapezoid dorsally (
<bibRefCitation id="76064B311F196D39AAAFF965FE31BAA8" author="Cao X. W. &amp; Li S. Q. &amp; Zabka M." box="[197,395,1714,1741]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="43 - 104" refId="ref8015" refString="Cao X. W., Li S. Q. &amp; Zabka M. 2016. The jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys 630: 43 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 630.8466" type="journal article" year="2016">
Cao 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39AB69F964FE81BAA9" box="[259,315,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) present in both sexes but more pronounced in females (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39AE3CF965FB07BAA9" box="[1110,1213,1714,1740]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[274,1314,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., Ƌ. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. Palp, ventral view. E. Palp, retrolateral view. The arrowheads point to the dorsal trapezoid (A) and black blotches (D). Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39AEA4F965FB4FBAA9" box="[1230,1269,1714,1740]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1386,302,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1398,302,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, ventral view. Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–D = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827807/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">3A</figureCitation>
). Prosoma broader than abdomen, eye field slightly elevated, sternum oval. Posterior margin of prosoma truncated. Pedicel obscured by anterior portion of abdomen. Abdomen elongated, tubular, broadest anteriorly and narrowing to posterior end with long spinnerets. Dorsum of abdomen with bright yellow or light brown markings (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39ABE5F896FE49BB39" box="[399,499,1857,1884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[274,1314,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., Ƌ. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. Palp, ventral view. E. Palp, retrolateral view. The arrowheads point to the dorsal trapezoid (A) and black blotches (D). Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F196D39A86BF895FD92BB39" box="[513,552,1858,1884]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[189,1386,302,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1398,302,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, ventral view. Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–D = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827807/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">3A</figureCitation>
). First pair of legs much darker than other pairs and more robust, with elongated femur I, patella I and tibia I. Tibia I with ventral spines in two rows of three each, metatarsi I with 2–2 ventral spines on distal half (
<bibRefCitation id="76064B311F196D39A8F9F85EFCF4BBC1" author="Cao X. W. &amp; Li S. Q. &amp; Zabka M." box="[659,846,1929,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="43 - 104" refId="ref8015" refString="Cao X. W., Li S. Q. &amp; Zabka M. 2016. The jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys 630: 43 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 630.8466" type="journal article" year="2016">
Cao 
<emphasis id="20E3EAD21F196D39A8A1F85DFD45BBC6" box="[715,767,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Embolus medium sized, straight and pointed, with or without retrolateral membranous margin, tegulum with broad posterior lobe with black blotches and well-developed prolateral lobe; RTA curved ventrally, medium-sized, slightly shorter than tibia (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F186D38AAAFFEDCFEB0BD40" box="[197,266,267,293]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,265,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[274,1314,265,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov., Ƌ. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. Palp, ventral view. E. Palp, retrolateral view. The arrowheads point to the dorsal trapezoid (A) and black blotches (D). Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–E = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827803/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 1</figureCitation>
<potCollectionCode id="C0C368CE1F186D38AB60FEDCFEFCBD40" box="[266,326,267,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C–E</potCollectionCode>
, 2 
<potCollectionCode id="C0C368CE1F186D38AB0AFEDCFE26BD40" box="[352,412,267,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">A–B</potCollectionCode>
). Epigynum with a pair of small, rounded atria at anterior portion and 
<potCollectionCode id="C0C368CE1F186D38AEBBFEDCFB40BD40" box="[1233,1274,267,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">CD</potCollectionCode>
with thick wall, spermathecae shape variable (
<figureCitation id="8AAC2A451F186D38A837FEF8FD1DBD2C" box="[605,679,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[248,1366,264,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[220,1367,242,1912]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Bavirecta flavopuncta sp. nov. A. Palp, ventral view. B. Palp, retrolateral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars: A–B = 0.2 mm; C–D = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3827805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3827805/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2</figureCitation>
<potCollectionCode id="C0C368CE1F186D38A8CDFEF8FD58BD2C" box="[679,738,303,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C–D</potCollectionCode>
, 3 
<potCollectionCode id="C0C368CE1F186D38A891FEF8FC83BD2C" box="[763,825,303,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C–D</potCollectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
